# Creative Docs — Priority Review Protocol

Applies whenever any file inside `creative/` is read, created, or edited.

## Obligation: re-review on every update

Any time a `creative/` doc is added to or modified — even a small addition — the
agent **must** do the following before finishing:

1. Re-read the entire doc.
2. Re-rate every idea using the **Priority Scale** below. Ratings can change as
   the game evolves — that is the point.
3. Update (or add) each idea's **Review block** (Pros / Cons-Risks / Notes).
4. Check whether the **Current Game Loop Snapshot** below needs updating. If the
   loop has materially changed (new system shipped, major mechanic changed), update
   it here and note the change.
5. If a previously "Long-term" idea has become actionable, escalate its rating
   and explain why in its Notes.

## Priority scale

| Rating | Meaning |
|--------|---------|
| **HIGH** | Directly strengthens the active game loop. High player-facing impact. Low-to-moderate implementation cost relative to return. Build soon. |
| **MEDIUM** | Valuable but not urgent. Complements the loop without being a gap. Can wait for a sprint gap or natural sequencing. |
| **LOW** | Polish, housekeeping, or timing-dependent. Do eventually, not now. |
| **LONG-TERM** | Depends on systems or content that don't exist yet. Document and design now; build later. |
| **DECISION FIRST** | Good idea but requires a design/product decision before any implementation. Flag the question to answer. |

## Current Game Loop Snapshot

*Update this section whenever a new system ships or a major mechanic changes.*

**Last updated: 2026-06-25**

### Layer 1 — Moment-to-moment (the click loop)
- Cursor over entity → tap (active/tap damage) or hover/lock (passive/hover damage)
- Hovering an entity reveals a sticky bottom-right hover preview bar (name, HP, reqs, XP, respawn, drops + drop %); replaces the old right-click Inspect popover (shipped v0.1.44, ADR-0028)
- Entity depletes → loot burst (items auto-awarded to Inventory) + Skill XP
- Entity respawns → repeat
- Loot presented as burst particles; no per-item queue or fanfare yet

### Layer 2 — Session progression
- Skill XP → Skill level (1–99, exponential curve) → one Skill Point per level
- Spend Skill Points in the Skill Tree → unlock Stat nodes (Tap Damage, Hover Damage, Hover Rate, Crit Chance, Crit Damage) and Tier unlock nodes
- Higher Tier entities require the matching Skill Tree to have unlocked that Tier
- Stats resolved at one choke point (`deriveStats`) — clean seam for future **Artifacts** (supersedes "Gear" framing; see `creative/design-ideas.md`)

### Layer 3 — Crafting, collection, and trade
- Gather resources → build Furnace → craft tools (tick-based, one job at a time) → claim from Shrine Offering
- Register gathered items into Collection Book Entries → Skill XP reward (more efficient than discarding but requires holding drops); registration now has rarity-tiered juice (slot slam + rarity flash, Rare+ panel shake) and an icon-first detail layout (shipped v0.1.44, see `creative/ux-housekeeping.md`)
- Black Market Vendor (General): tap to open a Shop scene and **Sell** surplus Items for Gold OR source-Skill XP (player's choice via a toggle); rarity-derived values; Epic/Legendary confirm (see ADR-0027)
- Gold now has a real source (sell-for-Gold) and a decision layer (Gold now vs XP now vs hold for a Collection); buying is a "coming soon" tab pending the **Artifacts** system
- No stack caps on gatherables; no drag-to-saw refinement loop yet

### Layer 4 — Idle / meta loop
- Broad Skill levelling auto-derives Clicker level (`floor(Σ skill levels / 10)`)
- Clicker Tree nodes → unlock general Idle Mode capability + per-Skill idle nodes
- Idle Mode: cursor detaches from pointer, auto-roams Level, gathers chosen Skill(s) hands-off
- Server-side (multiplayer tab stays gathering when backgrounded)

### Layer 5 — Social / multi-Level world
- Shared multiplayer world (`bigworld_01`, "The Clearing"), other cursors visible with nametags
- In-world Travel between Levels: Black Market via Beacon (ADR-0023), Deepwood via edge/signpost Travel with Arrival Anchors (ADR-0026)
- Per-player **Personal Breakables / Landmarks** (e.g. the Giant Stump): break state persists per player via an overlay (ADR-0025)
- Leaderboards: Woodcutting level, Mining level, Total level (global SQLite DO)
- Cursor skins as cosmetics, unlocked by Achievements

